Brunei Darussalam commemorates on Dec 1 the 75th anniversary of His Majesty’s Birth which began with the traditional Watap in conjunction with Maulidur Rasul at the Omar Ali Saifuddien Mosque in the capital yesterday morning.

The second day of Tahlil was held at the National Field in light of the current situation and as suggested by the Health Ministry.

The sultan maintained an impressive dedication and commitment to the well-being of his people and his country, and he has guided his nation through many challenges throughout his reign.

The Royal Duties and Civil Service Department (Jajat) wishes to inform that the curtain bazaar located at the corner of the Jalan Duta Staduim car parking lot will longer close on Dec 18, but rather it will continue to be carried until it is closed following the government’s instructions.

A delegation from the Guri Unit, Indonesian Armed Forces, travelled to Bandar Seri Begawan here to meet with a team from the National Disaster Management Centre (NDMC) at the JEMA building yesterday.
